, I looked more closely at the synchronization, and there may be some edge cases that aren't covered. Specifically:

* if {{close}} is holding the lock on {{openFileStreams}} while cleaning up, if another thread is waiting on its monitor then it may add elements to the collection after the filesystem is closed.
* In {{close}}, exceptions while closing streams may prevent the intended behavior. While {{close}} should be [idempotent|https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/io/Closeable.html#close--] (so a closed stream won't put this in an unrecoverable state), if any stream throws an exception, then subsequent entries will not be closed. The intended behavior is probably closer to {{IOUtils::cleanup}}, which swallows {{IOException}}.
* The lock order (i.e., hold {{openFileStreams}} while closing a stream, or hold one at at time) should be documented.
* {{openFileStreams}} can be a final field, Thanks [~chris.douglas] for comment.

 
